      <div id="center"><div id="squeeze"><div class="right-corner"><div class="left-corner">
          <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a></div>                              <h2>The Viscount&#039;s Unconventional Bride</h2>                                                  <div class="clear-block">
            <div id="node-60" class="node">



  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <p><img hspace="10" vspace="10" align="left" src="http://www.marynichols.co.uk/sites/default/files/Viscount%27s%20Bride.jpg" width="202" height="319" />published by Mills &amp; Boon</p>
<p>hardback March 2010, ISBN: 978 0 263 21449 9</p>
<p>paperback May 2010, ISBN: 978 0 263 87583 6</p>
<p>large print September 2010 ISBN: 978 0 263 21160 3</p>
<p><em>From runaway miss &ndash; to viscount&rsquo;s bride!</em></p>
<p>As a member of the renowned Piccadilly Gentlemen&rsquo;s Club, Jonathan Leinster has been instructed to ensure the return of a runaway. Little does he realise that meeting spirited Louise Vail will change his life for ever&hellip;</p>
<p>Having discovered she was adopted, Louise has fled to her birthplace, hoping to find her family &ndash; but handsome, charming Jonathan stops her in her tracks! His task is simple: escort Louise promptly home. Yet all he wants to do is claim her as his own!&nbsp;</p>
<p>This is the second in the series about the members of the Piccadilly Gentleman's Club, who are&nbsp;dedicated to restoring law and order to Georgian England.</p>
<p><em>Review:</em></p>
<p><em>This is a great follow-up to 'The Captain's Mysterious Lady' although it starts a bit slow it quickly gathers pace. I look forward to the next in the series. - Rita Read</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>  </div>

